title: 143rd meridian west
text:
The meridian 143° west of <a href="Prime%20Meridian">Greenwich</a> is a line of <a href="longitude">longitude</a> that extends from the <a href="North%20Pole">North Pole</a> across the <a href="Arctic%20Ocean">Arctic Ocean</a>, <a href="North%20America">North America</a>, the <a href="Pacific%20Ocean">Pacific Ocean</a>, the <a href="Southern%20Ocean">Southern Ocean</a>, and <a href="Antarctica">Antarctica</a> to the <a href="South%20Pole">South Pole</a>.
The 143rd meridian west line forms a <a href="great%20circle">great circle</a> with the <a href="37th%20meridian%20east">37th meridian east</a>.
From Pole to Pole.
